snippet.title: Weapons | Teaser
snippet.description:
This is where the story really starts.
#WeaponsMovie 

From New Line Cinema and Zach Cregger, the wholly original mind behind Barbarian, comes a new
horror/thriller: Weapons.

When all but one child from the same class mysteriously vanish on the same night at exactly the
same time, a community is left questioning who or what is behind their disappearance.
The film stars Josh Brolin, Julia Garner, Alden Ehrenreich, Austin Abrams, Cary Christopher, with
Benedict Wong, and Amy Madigan.

Cregger directs from his own screenplay, and also produces alongside Roy Lee, Miri Yoon, J.D.
Lifshitz and Raphael Margules, with Michelle Morrissey and Josh Brolin executive producing. The
filmmaker’s creative team behind the camera includes director of photography Larkin Seiple, production
designer Tom Hammock, editor Joe Murphy and costume designer Trish Sommerville. The music is by
Ryan Holladay, Hays Holladay and Zach Cregger.

New Line Cinema Presents a Subconscious/Vertigo Entertainment/Boulderlight Pictures
Production, a Zach Cregger Film, Weapons. It will be distributed by Warner Bros. Pictures, and released in
theaters and IMAX nationwide on August 8, 2025, and internationally beginning in August 2025.

snippet.title: The life of Pope Francis and its most important moments | DW Documentary
snippet.description:
Pope Francis has been spiritual leader of the Catholic Church since 2013. The name he chose as Pope refers to St Francis of Assisi. He set out to reform the Vatican; he advocated climate protection and inter-religious dialogue.

In March 2013, Jorge Mario Bergoglio from Argentina was elected 266th Pope, the first South American to become spiritual leader of the Catholic Church. He set out to reform the Vatican and the papal office, advocated climate protection and inter-religious dialogue.The name he chose toi be known by refers to St Francis of Assisi. Following "the little poor man’s” example, Bergoglio wanted a "poor church for the poor".

In memory of Pope Francis, Deutsche Welle is rebroadcasting the feature "Pope Francis — A Shepherd in the Storm.” On the occasion of the Pope's 85th birthday in December 2021 our report was an opportunity to take stock of his pontificate. What was this Pope able to change and reform; where were his limits? How did he lead the Catholic faith community through a time marked by crises and scandals? We gave people who knew Pope Francis personally, priests who advised him or were critical of his initiatives, and of course the Catholic laity, with their hopes and belief in a just pope, the opportunity to share their image of Pope Francis.

localized.description:
Pope Francis has been spiritual leader of the Catholic Church since 2013. The name he chose as Pope refers to St Francis of Assisi. He set out to reform the Vatican; he advocated climate protection and inter-religious dialogue.

In March 2013, Jorge Mario Bergoglio from Argentina was elected 266th Pope, the first South American to become spiritual leader of the Catholic Church. He set out to reform the Vatican and the papal office, advocated climate protection and inter-religious dialogue.The name he chose toi be known by refers to St Francis of Assisi. Following "the little poor man’s” example, Bergoglio wanted a "poor church for the poor".

In memory of Pope Francis, Deutsche Welle is rebroadcasting the feature "Pope Francis — A Shepherd in the Storm.” On the occasion of the Pope's 85th birthday in December 2021 our report was an opportunity to take stock of his pontificate. What was this Pope able to change and reform; where were his limits? How did he lead the Catholic faith community through a time marked by crises and scandals? We gave people who knew Pope Francis personally, priests who advised him or were critical of his initiatives, and of course the Catholic laity, with their hopes and belief in a just pope, the opportunity to share their image of Pope Francis.

snippet.title: After Pope Francis, what happens next? | ABC NEWS
snippet.description:
Following the passing of Pope Francis, a strict set of rules and protocols is set into motion, guiding the transition to the next Pope. This tradition traces its origins back to Saint Peter—the first Pope—believed to have been chosen by Jesus himself. 
Subscribe: http://ab.co/1svxLVE
Read more here: https://www.abc.net.au/news/2025-04-21/pope-francis-dies-catholic-church-vatican/103550594
Over the centuries, generations of Catholic leaders have refined the process into a meticulously choreographed and deeply internalized election. Ultimately, the Cardinals select one of their own to ascend as the moral and spiritual leader of the Catholic Church.

snippet.title: I Got a Pet Dragon...
snippet.description:
I got a pet dragon! And we're building him a $5,000 dream ecosystem. But will a dragon be a good pet?

There is a species of lizard that looks exactly like a real-life dragon: The red eyed crocodile skink! Watch to learn if keeping a pet dragon is a good idea...

♡ Get the merch: https://aquariuminfo.com/ (worldwide shipping 🌎)

SUBSCRIBE for a chance at the ecosystem kit
►  https://www.youtube.com/c/AquariumInfo?sub_confirmation=1

Meet The Crew!
🐈 Nori
🐲 Gizmo
🦀 Noodle & Pickle
🦞 Mochi
🐢 Harry 
🦐 Ralph
🐸 Frito & Burrito
🦎 Lucy & Lemon
🐠 Peanut & Jelly
🦎 Lime & Pepper & Squeak
🪦 R.I.P. Kirby

Today we buy the viral TikTok pet dragon and build its dream home ecosystem. This $5,000 terrarium has heaps of live plants, a pond filled with real fish and even a giant castle! 

In this adventure-filled episode, we get the viral exotic pet that looks like a real dragon: a red eyed crocodile skink! We also build a DIY 3D printed castle for him to explore, travel to the desert to find dragons in the wild and even feed my rescue pet Alaskan King Crab in the studio! 

Watch until the end to see my pet dragon Gizmo explore his 3D printed Disney-style castle! This video is perfect for anyone who loves exotic pets, rare animals, DIY projects or is just interested in what it takes to keep a dragon as a pet! 

If you have any comments, suggestions or questions for this pet dragon video or future videos, leave them down in the comments! Also for additional content like this, video tutorials, project sneak peeks and more, follow me on Instagram @aquariuminfo.

If you're reading this, you're a Super Fan!
Comment "King Gizmo" so I notice you 👑🐉

snippet.title: Game 1 Reactions: Lakers BLOWN OUT vs. Wolves, Warriors-Rockets, Clippers-Nuggets | NBA Playoffs
snippet.description:
Nick Wright reacts to Steph Curry, Jimmy Butler, and the Golden State Warriors' 95-85 win over the Houston Rockets in Game 1 of their NBA Playoffs series. Is Nick ready to change his pick from Houston to Golden State? Later, Nick reacts to LeBron James, Luka Doncic, and the Los Angeles Lakers' 117-95 loss to Anthony Edwards and the Minnesota Timberwolves. Are the Lakers in more danger than Nick originally thought? Nick then breaks down Pistons-Knicks, Clippers-Nuggets, and more from the NBA Playoffs!

snippet.title: 24hrs Flying First Class from Australia to England
snippet.description:
Use code trektrendy at the link below to get an exclusive 60% off an annual Incogni plan: https://incogni.com/trektrendy

Today i'm flying First Class for the next 24 hours onboard both Singapore Airlines A380 Suites & British Airways new Suites with closing doors. I'll document exactly what it's like to make the iconic journey from Sydney, Australia all the way to London, England. 

From an overview of the various facilities onboard, the seats / beds themselves to the food & entertainment provided. What's more I've booked the luxurious Marina Bay Sands hotel in Singapore for our layover so expect a walkthrough of this 5* property. 

Of course all of this does not come cheap, but as usual I've paid in full for both of our tickets to remain impartial and unbiased about the experience in flying up front. 

0:00 - Introduction
04:01 - BA First Class
08:42 - Luxury Layover 
11:10 - Singapore First Class
18:20 - The Bed
21:09 - Cost

snippet.title: Canada election 2025: English language leaders' debate | FULL
snippet.description:
Liberal Leader Mark Carney sought to cast himself as a safe choice to guide Canada through a crisis during the English-language debate on Thursday evening.

Carney, currently leading in the polls, was the primary target during the final debate of the election, with his chief rival Conservative Party Leader Pierre Poilievre trying to paint him as “more of the same” following a decade of Liberal leadership.

“Mr. Carney, Justin Trudeau’s staffers are actually here with you at this debate in Montreal, writing the talking points that you are regurgitating into the microphone,” he said.

Carney, who tried to differentiate himself from former prime minister Justin Trudeau, retorted: “Look, I do my own talking points thank you.”

Later in the debate, NDP Leader Jagmeet Singh accused Carney of failing to defend Canadian jobs threatened by U.S. tariffs.

Bloc Quebecois Leader Yves-Francois Blanchet, meanwhile, argued that Carney must disclose his financial assets to show he’s better than Trudeau, picking up on an issue that has dogged Carney throughout the campaign.

7:51 Debate begins
8:39 Tariffs and threats to Canada
26:07 Affordability and the cost of living

snippet.title: Simulating an Ant Colony For 100 Days
snippet.description:
Merch (new axolotl hoodie): https://terragreenstore.com/

In this video I got a queen trap-jaw ant and raised it into an entire ant colony! Throughout the video I simulated real world events to see how the ants would react. The ending was not what I was expecting... but it should make for another good video. 

If I used any of your copyrighted material in the video and you are not okay with it, please contact me on my business email found in my channel's description so we can reach an agreement.

Thanks for watching and please subscribe!

#ants #antcolony
